      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Using Travel Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The UAE requires proper health insurance, not travel insurance. Your policy must meet DHA/HAAD standards. Travel insurance will be rejected at the visa stage.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Underestimating Living Costs</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Dubai is expensive. If you're earning $4,000/month, you'll spend most of it on living costs. The tax savings are meaningful only at higher income levels.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Missing the 60-Day Entry Window</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">Your entry permit expires 60 days after issue. If you don't enter within this window, you'll need to reapply. Plan your travel accordingly.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Forgetting Medical Test</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The medical fitness test is mandatory after arrival. Don't delay—complete it within the first few days to avoid complications with visa stamping.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="border-l-4 border-red-500 pl-4">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900">Trying to Work with UAE Clients</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">The Virtual Working Visa is for remote work with foreign employers only. To work with UAE clients, you need a freelancer visa or business license.</p>
      </div>

