  <!-- Section: FAQ -->
  <section id="faq" class="scroll-mt-24 mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I really pay zero income tax in the UAE?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. The UAE has no personal income tax. Your foreign salary is 100% yours. However, you may still have tax obligations in your home country—US citizens, for example, must file regardless of residence. Consult a tax professional.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I bring my family on the Virtual Working Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. You can sponsor dependents (spouse, children) once your visa is active. Each dependent requires additional fees and insurance. The income requirement doesn't increase per dependent.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I open a UAE bank account?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. With your Emirates ID and residence visa, you can open local bank accounts. Popular options include Emirates NBD, Mashreq, and digital banks like Liv (by Emirates NBD). Requirements vary by bank.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about the social and cultural environment?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The UAE is cosmopolitan and tolerant of expats. Alcohol is available in licensed venues. Dress codes are relaxed in tourist areas but more conservative in local neighborhoods. Ramadan brings some restrictions. Overall, most expats find it comfortable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can I travel while on the Virtual Working Visa?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          Yes. You can travel freely in and out of the UAE. There's no minimum stay requirement. Many digital nomads use Dubai as a hub, traveling frequently while maintaining UAE residence.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-neutral-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What happens after one year?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-600">
          The Virtual Working Visa is renewable annually as long as you continue to meet the income requirements. After extended residence, you may explore other visa options like the Green Visa (5 years) if you qualify.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

